column13:
1. Societal Impact:

i. Enhances public health and hygiene by reducing human contact with waste.

ii. Educates communities about waste categorization and promotes eco-conscious behavior.

iii. Empowers municipalities with data-driven insights for better planning and resource allocation.

2. Industrial Impact:

i. Offers a scalable solution for smart cities, municipalities, and waste management companies.

ii. Reduces labor costs and operational inefficiencies in waste handling.

iii. Enables real-time monitoring and automation, improving compliance with environmental regulations.

3. Contribution to New Knowledge:

i. Demonstrates the integration of computer vision and sensor fusion in environmental applications.

ii. Adds to the field of AI-driven sustainable technologies with a real-world deployment model.

iii. Provides a foundation for future research in automated material recovery, smart recycling, and robotics in waste management.

column4: Image Processing{enhancemeant,denoising} using Multiscale transform (Matlab,Paython Software )
column5:
Image denoising plays very crucial role in applications which include photography/videography, Security-Surveillance, Medical Image analysis, Astronomy, Aerial photography, Satellite Imagery, and many more. The results of denoising also affect the accuracy of later tasks of image segmentation, object recognition, classification.
In this project we explore image denoising of different images with different noises using multiscale transform such as wavelet transform, ridgelet transform, curvelet transform and shearlet transform and several thresholding techniques such as hard thresholding, soft thresholding, SUREShrink, VisuShrink and BayesShrink etc. Further, we compare the performance of these methods or transform in terms of PSNR and MSE values and aim to provide better image denoising technique for images.

column13:
The outcome is expected to contribute:

To Industry: By improving visual data preprocessing pipelines in domains such as healthcare diagnostics, satellite image interpretation, and security surveillance, leading to more accurate and reliable decision-making.

To Society: Through enhanced image quality in daily applications such as mobile photography, video streaming, and medical diagnostics, ultimately improving user experience and diagnostic precision.

To New Knowledge: By offering comparative insights into the performance of different multiscale transforms and thresholding methods, the research contributes to the academic understanding and future development of efficient image denoising algorithms.

In general, this work promotes innovation in digital imaging and lays the groundwork for robust, noise-resilient image processing systems.
